# FEATURE ENGINEERING.
# I found out some features seem to have relevent to each other like(GarageArea, GarageCars),(X1stFlrSF, X2ndFlrSF).
In [403]:
# FEATURE ENGINEERING(GarageArea, GarageCars).
GarageArea_per_Cars <- (train$GarageArea)/(train$GarageCars)

LM_model_new1 <- lm(SalePrice ~ GarageCars+ GarageArea, 
               data = train)
LM_model_new1.1 <- lm(SalePrice ~ GarageArea_per_Cars, 
                      data = train)

mean(LM_model_new1$residuals^2)
mean(LM_model_new1.1$residuals^2)

# Conclusion: The new MSE is greater than the previous one, hence it's a useless new feature.
3614729651.10643
6185595786.25904
In [404]:
# FEATURE ENGINEERING(X1stFlrSF, X2ndFlrSF).
Total_FlrSF <- (train$X2ndFlrSF)+(train$X1stFlrSF)

LM_model_new2 <- lm(SalePrice ~ X1stFlrSF, 
                    data = train)
LM_model_new2.1 <- lm(SalePrice ~ Total_FlrSF,
                      data = train)

mean(LM_model_new2$residuals^2)
mean(LM_model_new2.1$residuals^2)

# Conclusion: The new MSE is smaller than the previous one, hence it's a meaningful new feature.
